x4freetext: Runs were made with several sample
thicknesses. The peak of the low-energy resonance was
run with three very thin gold foils. The resolution
that can be achieved using the 2461 planes of a Be
monochromator is higher than any previously used.
These planes give a Bragg angle of ten degrees for
the 4.91-eV neutrons at the center of the resonance.
